"Then," she paced around him, "I do believe that disabling it of any weapons 
along with disorientation is some damage you can do to this 'guest'. The 
other is to make sure whatever cell you have is able to withstand anything." 

Stopping to look at Hydras. "I've seen too many mistakes in the past. I don't 
make the same mistake twice." her icy blue eyes gazing at him more to assist 
him with wisdom than to growl at him. She would hate to see him... 
terminated. She had to deal with all the pain before with Megatron, then 
Galvatron. She was not willing to deal with more pain.
